(75178, 'EDA4898D-469C-4B23-8C06-6ED622F98732', 'Morning love. While we weren’t able to celebrate our (other?) anniversary together, i want to close this calendar year celebrating you and my deep love and appreciation for you. My covid imposed retreat forced more alone time and still time (and feeling crappy time) than I wanted this week…and it was an important reminder of all of the daily moments I cherish together. Holding you in bed with my arm and leg wrapped around you when we fall asleep, and for a few minutes before we get out of bed, the few moments of waffle time with you and orli as we start the day, your meticulous planning (and reminding to me) of the nuts and bolts of logistics…to get the most out of the day and to keep us functioning and able to experience so many wonderful people and places and things….which I do not take for granted, the moments I can listen into a call, hearing you bring your many gifts to your work, walking past the air fryer with your gigantic mound of roasted veggies cooking…or cooling (because you didn’t get to them yet), listening to you laugh with orli as she finds new hilarious ways to brighten our world, seeing you walking around without any clothes and thinking, holy hell…hotness…how did I get so lucky. I can go on and on. I feel so blessed and extremely lucky for every day I get to be in the world with you as my partner. There have been many hard moments this year…many where I have caused you great pain and annoyance. Thank you for your grace and compassion and abiding love. We share a hunger and curiousity to experience the world and grow and give in different ways. But you never cease to inspire and push me toward being a better human, husband, lover, father, learner, friend and force in the world. I love you so so much and can’t wait for everything that awaits us in the coming year.  Love you to the moon and back. ', '725727742109061760', 'None', 1, 'David', 'Nitzan', 0, '', '', '', 'iMessage', 'E:nwdave@b-zb.com', 'Dav